==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mantua
<hw>Man"tu*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
superior kind of rich silk formerly exported from Mantua in Italy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beck (Draper's Dict.).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A woman's cloak or mantle; also, a woman's
gown.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mantuamaker</ent>⟦br⟧
